sentence: Looking at the universe of stocks we cover at Dividend Channel, on 12/4/19, Fanhua Inc (Symbol: FANH), Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), and Jack in the Box, Inc. (Symbol: JACK) will all trade ex-dividend for their respective upcoming dividends.

Fanhua Inc will pay its quarterly dividend of $0.30 on 12/19/19, Home Depot Inc will pay its quarterly dividend of $1.36 on 12/19/19, and Jack in the Box, Inc. will pay its quarterly dividend of $0.40 on 12/20/19.

As a percentage of FANH's recent stock price of $26.92, this dividend works out to approximately 1.11%, so look for shares of Fanhua Inc to trade 1.11% lower — all else being equal — when FANH shares open for trading on 12/4/19.
Similarly, investors should look for HD to open 0.62% lower in price and for JACK to open 0.50% lower, all else being equal.

In general, dividends are not always predictable, following the ups and downs of company profits over time.
Therefore, a good first due diligence step in forming an expectation of annual yield going forward, is looking at the history above, for a sense of stability over time.
This can help in judging whether the most recent dividends from these companies are likely to continue.
If they do continue, the current estimated yields on annualized basis would be 4.46% for Fanhua Inc, 2.47% for Home Depot Inc, and 2.01% for Jack in the Box, Inc..
In Monday trading, Fanhua Inc shares are currently down about 1%, Home Depot Inc shares are down about 0.3%, and Jack in the Box, Inc. shares are up about 0.6% on the day.
